	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=736><span id=Sage>ArtulynStarsummoner</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>149 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.85]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The superpatch of Oct'99 removed both the Manastone and Box of Abu'Kar (sp) but it also introduced the Temple of Solusek Ro and all of it's class armor quests that were eventually improved upon with Kunark armor drops, Velious armor quests and finally the Ornate and Elemental armors of PoP. The crafted armor quests in SK for warriors were the test and template for the Sol Ro armor quests.<br><br>The expansion nerf to the manastone was about the same time that the plane of sky went live if not shortly thereafter. It was definately pre-Kunark that they announced it would no longer work in the outer planes or in any EQ expansion because it was just so unbalancing in the hands of a CH capable cleric.<br><br>The pre-PoP T-rod nerf was done for similar reasons, an endless manapool trivializes way too much content and takes the challenge out of many encounters.<br><br>The only way anyone can get one nowadays is if someone sells their old manastone.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Sage Artulyn Starsummoner 65 Arch Convoker of The Dedicated on Bertoxxulous<br>For the Light of a Candle to be Seen, It must be taken to a Dark Place -- UKLG</td></tr>
